David Stow has lived in Davis for 18 years.  He is the owner of ArcDeZign, an architect architecture firm in Davis which specializes in custom homes and residential remodeling design.  He has extensive design experience in residential, commercial, and transportation architecture.  David is a graduate of the UC Berkeley University of California, Berkeley, from which he received his Bachelor of Architecture degree.  He is married to Users/SallyStow Sally Stow, Director of the Gifted Child Institute, Davis, and has one son, Brandon Stow, who is a software engineer in San Jose.
